            <title><![CDATA[Nintendo's Big Switch 2 Reveal, Pre-Orders Delayed Due To Trump's Tariffs, And More Of The Week's Big News]]></title>
            <link>https://kotaku.com/nintendo-switch-2-direct-trump-tariffs-preorders-1851774807</link>
            <guid>https://www.resetera.com/threads/nintendos-big-switch-2-reveal-pre-orders-delayed-due-to-trumps-tariffs-and-more-of-the-weeks-big-news.1156077/</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[https://kotaku.com/nintendo-switch-2-direct-trump-tariffs-preorders-1851774807<br/><br/><div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div><div><figure id="" data-id="3fd52a5c7365a7310b6279132bb15b78" data-recommend-id="image://3fd52a5c7365a7310b6279132bb15b78" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="false" data-imagerights="in-house-art" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Nintendo<!-- -->, <!-- -->Nintendo / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Nintendo / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->NetEase / Marvel / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->FromSoftware<!-- -->, <!-- -->Photo<!-- -->: <!-- -->Andrew Harnik / Nintendo / Kotaku<!-- --> (<!-- -->Getty Images<!-- -->)<!-- -->, <!-- -->David Ryder<!-- --> (<!-- -->Getty Images<!-- -->)<!-- -->, <!-- -->Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Nintendo / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Nintendo / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Nintendo / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="3fd52a5c7365a7310b6279132bb15b78" data-recommend-id="image://3fd52a5c7365a7310b6279132bb15b78" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Finally this week, Nintendo pulled back the curtain on the Switch 2 in a big way, giving us details about its screen, specs, and some of the games we can expect to see at launch and in the months that follow. A few days later, however, the company announced that preorders, previously set to go live on April 9, were being pushed back so that Nintendo could “assess the potential impact of tariffs and evolving market conditions.” Read on for these stories and lots more details about the Switch 2 and everything we saw in Nintendo’s big Direct presentation.</p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="485ec87fd3cea832387b2699e4cbd2a1" data-recommend-id="image://485ec87fd3cea832387b2699e4cbd2a1" data-format="jpg" data-width="2400" data-height="1350" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A Switch 2 with its Joy-Cons detatched." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A Switch 2 with its Joy-Cons detatched." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Nintendo</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="485ec87fd3cea832387b2699e4cbd2a1" data-recommend-id="image://485ec87fd3cea832387b2699e4cbd2a1" data-format="jpg" data-width="2400" data-height="1350" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A Switch 2 with its Joy-Cons detatched." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Console pre-orders are a notoriously painful process. If you’re trying to get them online, scalpers and bots are likely to snatch them up at stores like Target or Best Buy. With <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/nintendo-switch-2-price-release-date-specs-1851773502&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/nintendo-switch-2-price-release-date-specs-1851773502">the Switch 2 coming in hot</a></span>, Nintendo is putting some restrictions in place on its online store to hopefully make sure people who actually want to buy and own the new console can get it, rather than predatory resellers who will charge you twice as much on eBay. But they’re uh, pretty restrictive, to the point where even the most dedicated Nintendo fan might not be able to buy directly from the company. - Kenneth Shepard <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/nintendo-switch-2-pre-order-requirements-store-online-1851774277&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/nintendo-switch-2-pre-order-requirements-store-online-1851774277">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="6b744692b3848d903f06f26a655c3065" data-recommend-id="image://6b744692b3848d903f06f26a655c3065" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Nintendo / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="6b744692b3848d903f06f26a655c3065" data-recommend-id="image://6b744692b3848d903f06f26a655c3065" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Today, <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/switch-2-reveal-nintendo-direct-mario-donkey-kong-1851774194&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/switch-2-reveal-nintendo-direct-mario-donkey-kong-1851774194">Nintendo revealed all about the Switch 2</a></span>. The new console is set to launch in June and will cost $450. And it will, as previously announced, support most OG Switch games. However, two new compatibility lists from Nintendo seem to indicate that over 100 Switch games will have various issues or just flat-out not work on the upcoming Switch 2. - Zack Zwiezen <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/switch-2-backwards-compatibility-list-start-up-issues-1851774297&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/switch-2-backwards-compatibility-list-start-up-issues-1851774297">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="b7aa7a09b26f83b2df44e14d6531e5be" data-recommend-id="image://b7aa7a09b26f83b2df44e14d6531e5be" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Trump fist bumps escalating Switch 2 prices. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Trump fist bumps escalating Switch 2 prices. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="getty" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Photo<!-- -->: <!-- -->Andrew Harnik / Nintendo / Kotaku<!-- --> (<!-- -->Getty Images<!-- -->)</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="b7aa7a09b26f83b2df44e14d6531e5be" data-recommend-id="image://b7aa7a09b26f83b2df44e14d6531e5be" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Trump fist bumps escalating Switch 2 prices. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Fans faced a bit of sticker shock today when <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/nintendo-switch-2-price-release-date-specs-1851773502&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/nintendo-switch-2-price-release-date-specs-1851773502">Nintendo revealed the Switch 2 would cost $450</a></span>, especially with some new physical games set to cost as much as $90. But the price of upgrading to the <em>Mario </em>maker’s next console generation is set to get even worse after President Donald Trump announced a new wave of <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/tariffs-trump-games-digital-consoles-price-increase-ps5-1851767919?_gl=1*45ywdo*_ga*MTc0MjY2NTg1OS4xNzQwMzc1OTc4*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTc0MzYyODk3Mi41NS4xLjE3NDM2MjkxNzIuNTguMC4w&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/tariffs-trump-games-digital-consoles-price-increase-ps5-1851767919?_gl=1*45ywdo*_ga*MTc0MjY2NTg1OS4xNzQwMzc1OTc4*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTc0MzYyODk3Mi41NS4xLjE3NDM2MjkxNzIuNTguMC4w">shockingly high tariffs</a></span> that could push the price of a Switch 2 in the U.S. to over $600.  - Ethan Gach <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/switch-2-price-trump-tariffs-vietnam-china-trade-war-1851774438&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/switch-2-price-trump-tariffs-vietnam-china-trade-war-1851774438">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="d54eb5c981c30b9b79f7b3b8ca6c13ce" data-recommend-id="image://d54eb5c981c30b9b79f7b3b8ca6c13ce" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Nintendo's splash page for the Switch 2, with the release date underneath, June 5." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Nintendo's splash page for the Switch 2, with the release date underneath, June 5." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Nintendo / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="d54eb5c981c30b9b79f7b3b8ca6c13ce" data-recommend-id="image://d54eb5c981c30b9b79f7b3b8ca6c13ce" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Nintendo's splash page for the Switch 2, with the release date underneath, June 5." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>It’s happening! It’s official! We now finally know nearly everything important about the Switch 2. In today’s Switch 2 Direct, Nintendo broke down details of what the console will offer, what specs it offers, and when it’ll be available to buy. - John Walker <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/nintendo-switch-2-price-release-date-specs-1851773502&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/nintendo-switch-2-price-release-date-specs-1851773502">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="0298fbaa86a0bca10612df037bf69a2b" data-recommend-id="image://0298fbaa86a0bca10612df037bf69a2b" data-format="png" data-width="2560" data-height="1440" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Donkey Kong punches his way towards the screen." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Donkey Kong punches his way towards the screen." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Nintendo / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="0298fbaa86a0bca10612df037bf69a2b" data-recommend-id="image://0298fbaa86a0bca10612df037bf69a2b" data-format="png" data-width="2560" data-height="1440" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Donkey Kong punches his way towards the screen." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Today was the day Nintendo finally shared with us a much-needed deep dive on the highly anticipated successor to its wildly successful hybrid console, the Switch. The Switch 2 was proudly shown off by the company during a Direct and at long last we got a look at some upcoming games, what makes this machine unique from its predecessor, and just what the heck that C button is all about. - Claire Jackson <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/switch-2-reveal-nintendo-direct-mario-donkey-kong-1851774194&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/switch-2-reveal-nintendo-direct-mario-donkey-kong-1851774194">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="3270cc0f221d1184b130887535cf499f" data-recommend-id="image://3270cc0f221d1184b130887535cf499f" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A Nintendo sign is displayed. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A Nintendo sign is displayed. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="getty" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Photo<!-- -->: <!-- -->David Ryder<!-- --> (<!-- -->Getty Images<!-- -->)</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="3270cc0f221d1184b130887535cf499f" data-recommend-id="image://3270cc0f221d1184b130887535cf499f" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A Nintendo sign is displayed. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Switch 2 pre-orders were supposed to begin on April 9. No longer. In an unprecedented move, Nintendo announced on Friday that it’s halting pre-orders for <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/nintendo-switch-2-price-release-date-specs-1851773502&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/nintendo-switch-2-price-release-date-specs-1851773502">its upcoming $450 hardware launch</a></span> because of new tariffs in the U.S. set to go into effect on April 5.  - Ethan Gach <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/switch-2-preorder-price-tariff-trump-nintendo-1851774764&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/switch-2-preorder-price-tariff-trump-nintendo-1851774764">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="eeceb5615cd6ca226d9fb8c7b1810f0b" data-recommend-id="image://eeceb5615cd6ca226d9fb8c7b1810f0b" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->NetEase / Marvel / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="eeceb5615cd6ca226d9fb8c7b1810f0b" data-recommend-id="image://eeceb5615cd6ca226d9fb8c7b1810f0b" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>On April 3, NetEase revealed the next season of <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/games/marvel-rivals?startIndex=10&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/games/marvel-rivals?startIndex=10"><em>Marvel Rivals</em></a></span>. The popular game’s second season starts April 11 and will add Emma Frost and Ultron to the already large roster of <em>Marvel Rivals. </em> - Zack Zwiezen <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-frost-ultron-characters-xmen-season-2-1851774548&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-frost-ultron-characters-xmen-season-2-1851774548">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="799e09180d247ed0509ab91c751e1d18" data-recommend-id="image://799e09180d247ed0509ab91c751e1d18" data-format="jpg" data-width="2560" data-height="1440" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A character from The Duskbloods." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A character from The Duskbloods." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="false" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->FromSoftware</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="799e09180d247ed0509ab91c751e1d18" data-recommend-id="image://799e09180d247ed0509ab91c751e1d18" data-format="jpg" data-width="2560" data-height="1440" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A character from The Duskbloods." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>One of the biggest announcements during Nintendo’s Switch 2 Direct wasn’t a Nintendo game or major feature reveal for the system. Instead, it was from <em>Elden Ring </em>developer FromSoftware, who closed out the showcase’s partner segment by revealing <em>The Duskbloods</em>, a new Soulslike from the team that will be exclusive to the Nintendo Switch 2. - Kenneth Shepard <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/duskbloods-switch-2-nintendo-fromsoftware-exclusive-1851774242&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/duskbloods-switch-2-nintendo-fromsoftware-exclusive-1851774242">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="55d556c4b784d376f40c724d39551681" data-recommend-id="image://55d556c4b784d376f40c724d39551681" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Chibbi Robot catches on fire because of the Switch 2's battery life. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Chibbi Robot catches on fire because of the Switch 2's battery life. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Nintendo / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="55d556c4b784d376f40c724d39551681" data-recommend-id="image://55d556c4b784d376f40c724d39551681" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Chibbi Robot catches on fire because of the Switch 2's battery life. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Battery life for gaming handhelds is always a challenge but the tradeoffs for the Switch 2 appear to be particularly brutal. <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/nintendo-switch-2-price-release-date-specs-1851773502?_gl=1*vmt1g3*_ga*MTc0MjY2NTg1OS4xNzQwMzc1OTc4*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTc0MzU5OTQwMC41My4xLjE3NDM2MjExNDguNDYuMC4w&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/nintendo-switch-2-price-release-date-specs-1851773502?_gl=1*vmt1g3*_ga*MTc0MjY2NTg1OS4xNzQwMzc1OTc4*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTc0MzU5OTQwMC41My4xLjE3NDM2MjExNDguNDYuMC4w">Nintendo has confirmed that the next-gen device</a></span> will run for anywhere from 2-6.5 hours on a single charge depending on what you’re playing. It ain’t great. In fact, it’s somehow even worse than that of the original Switch. - Ethan Gach <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/switch-2-battery-life-steam-deck-compares-4k-60fps-1851774376&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/switch-2-battery-life-steam-deck-compares-4k-60fps-1851774376">Read More</a></span></p></div></div></div>]]></content:encoded>
